{"word":"ἄνειμι","slug":"ἄνειμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄνειμι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>εῖμι</el>, <i>ibo</i>, in attic serving as <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> to <a href='S:ἀνέρχομαι'><el>ἀνέρχομαι</el></a>.\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to go up</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἅμ' ἠελίωι ἀνιόντι</el> at sun- <i>rise</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to sail up</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>out to sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to go up inland</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> into Central Asia, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to approach</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> as a suppliant, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to go back, go home, return</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}